# Buffered List

Buffered List is a linked list of byte slice with fixed length.

The length is `os.Getpagesize()` value.

## install

`go get -u github.com/snowmerak/bufferedlist`

## use

```go
package main

import (
	"crypto/rand"
	"fmt"
	"os"

	"github.com/snowmerak/bufferedlist"
)

func main() {
	list := bufferedlist.New()

	b := make([]byte, os.Getpagesize()*2/3)
	for i := 0; i < 2; i++ {
		rand.Read(b[:])
		list.Append(b)
	}

	length := 0
	r := [1000]byte{}
	for !list.IsEmpty() {
		n := list.Read(r[:])
		length += n
		fmt.Printf("%d: %v\n", n, r[:n])
	}
	fmt.Println("length:", length)
}
```
